# M6 P07 — movement probe (current behavior baseline).
#
# Single experiment: a running jump on flat ground. Measure horizontal
# distance covered during the airborne window. SHOT_LOG already records
# per-tick pelvis pos for the local mech via main.c's test-play branch
# (gated on g_shot_mode), and apply_jump emits a SHOT_LOG when the jump
# impulse fires.
#
# Expected (post Phase 2 — air add-toward-target):
#   RUN_SPEED_PXS = 280, JUMP_IMPULSE_PXS = 320, GRAVITY = 1080 px/s²,
#   AIR_ACCEL_PXS2 = 1680 (~10 frames to RUN_SPEED in air, ~0.6× ground).
#   Apex height = 320² / (2·1080) ≈ 47 px above ground.
#   Time to apex = 320 / 1080 ≈ 0.30 s ≈ 18 ticks at 60 Hz.
#   Full airborne window ≈ 36 ticks.
#   Running jump: horizontal momentum preserved at the ground→air boundary
#   because input is a CAP (not a target). vx decays only via the
#   universal 0.99/tick drag — ~3.15 px/tick by tick 140 from ~4.17 at
#   the jump moment. Horizontal travel in air with right held ≈ 100-110 px
#   (vs ~52 px under the pre-Phase-2 AIR_CONTROL=0.35 SET-velocity clamp).

window 1280 720
seed 1 0
out build/shots/m6_movement_probe
spawn_at 400 600
aim 1100 600

# (a) Establish ground state — no input.
at  20 shot stand_t020
at  40 shot stand_t040

# (b) Start running right, jump 30 ticks in. Hold BTN_JUMP across a
# 6-tick window — `tap` is single-tick and the running gait briefly
# lifts feet off the ground every 5-6 ticks; a 1-tick press can miss
# the grounded=1 window. The jump path (`mech.c:1022`) only fires
# when `(in.buttons & BTN_JUMP) && grounded` are both true on the
# same tick, but it's edge-effectively-single-shot once the mech
# leaves the ground (so the hold doesn't double-jump).
at  60 press right
at  80 shot run_t020
at 100 shot run_t040
at 108 press jump
at 115 release jump
at 115 shot jump_t005
at 120 shot jump_t010
at 125 shot jump_t015
at 130 shot jump_t020
at 135 shot jump_t025
at 140 shot jump_t030
at 145 shot jump_t035
at 150 shot landed_t040

# (c) Keep running through the landing and a few ticks past so the
# logger captures momentum decay (or lack thereof).
at 180 shot postland_t030
at 220 release right
at 240 shot stopped_t020

contact_sheet probe_sheet cols 5

at 280 end
